The paper deals with multi-resource allocation in cloud computing systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses fairness and strategy-proofness, which are concepts related to Game Theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic design and analysis aspects of the paper suggest that it could also belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the implementation and performance evaluation of the proposed mechanism could also make it relevant to the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
